Polycrates of Samos was called ‘the fortunate.’ Not a single untoward circum· stance had ever befallen him, except that he had thrown his favourite ring overboard at sea.b Did that single annoyance then make him unfortunate? and did he become fortunate again when the very same ring was found in a fish’s belly?
